.Ip "$^E" 8
.IX Item "$^E"
.PD
Error information specific to the current operating system.  At
the moment, this differs from \f(CW\*(C`$!\*(C'\fR under only \s-1VMS\s0, \s-1OS/2\s0, and Win32
(and for MacPerl).  On all other platforms, \f(CW\*(C`$^E\*(C'\fR is always just
the same as \f(CW\*(C`$!\*(C'\fR.
.Sp
Under \s-1VMS\s0, \f(CW\*(C`$^E\*(C'\fR provides the \s-1VMS\s0 status value from the last
system error.  This is more specific information about the last
system error than that provided by \f(CW\*(C`$!\*(C'\fR.  This is particularly
important when \f(CW\*(C`$!\*(C'\fR is set to \fB\s-1EVMSERR\s0\fR.
.Sp
Under \s-1OS/2\s0, \f(CW\*(C`$^E\*(C'\fR is set to the error code of the last call to
\&\s-1OS/2\s0 \s-1API\s0 either via \s-1CRT\s0, or directly from perl.
.Sp
