reported by the Win32 call \f(CW\*(C`GetLastError()\*(C'\fR which describes
the last error from within the Win32 \s-1API\s0.  Most Win32\-specific
code will report errors via \f(CW\*(C`$^E\*(C'\fR.  \s-1ANSI\s0 C and Unix-like calls
set \f(CW\*(C`errno\*(C'\fR and so most portable Perl code will report errors
via \f(CW\*(C`$!\*(C'\fR. 
.Sp
Caveats mentioned in the description of \f(CW\*(C`$!\*(C'\fR generally apply to
\&\f(CW\*(C`$^E\*(C'\fR, also.  (Mnemonic: Extra error explanation.)
